{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TK8wd92JDfXyknycussato","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Detailed Project Analysis:\n\n1. Project Structure:\nThis is a Quarkus-based Pet Clinic application with a comprehensive structure:\n- Maven-based project\n- Quarkus framework\n- Multi-profile configuration (dev, test, prod)\n- RESTful API with JAX-RS\n- Hibernate ORM with Panache\n- Multilingual support\n- Kubernetes and container image configuration\n\n2. Build System (pom.xml):\n- Java 21 \n- Quarkus Platform version 3.30.5\n- Dependencies include:\n  * Quarkus REST\n  * Hibernate ORM Panache\n  * PostgreSQL JDBC\n  * H2 for dev/test\n  * Kubernetes and container image support\n  * WebJars for frontend dependencies\n  * JUnit5 and REST Assured for testing\n\n3. Database Configuration:\n- Dev/Test: H2 in-memory database\n- Production: PostgreSQL\n- Configured with different connection parameters per profile\n- Automatic schema generation \n- SQL logging enabled\n\n4. Application Components:\nMain domains:\n- Owners\n- Pets\n- Veterinarians\n- Visits\n\n5. Kubernetes and Containerization:\n- Docker Compose configuration\n- Kubernetes deployment files\n- Native image support\n- Container image configured for quay.io registry\n\n6. Internationalization:\n- Supports multiple locales\n- Contains Spanish message bundle\n\n7. Testing:\n- Integration and unit tests for resources\n- Uses JUnit5 and REST Assured\n\nKey Interesting Files:\n- pom.xml (build configuration)\n- application.properties (runtime configuration)\n- docker-compose.yml (container orchestration)\n- src/main/kubernetes/* (Kubernetes deployment configs)\n\nWould you like me to dive deeper into any specific aspect of this project?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"0635e9f9-01ad-4989-ac54-f7eb591248c5"}
