{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018vevEE6P1dUWjnDeHWa83M","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic;\n     2→\n     3→import io.smallrye.common.annotation.Blocking;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→\n     6→/**\n     7→ * Used to ensure that all endpoints are blocking by default\n     8→ */\n     9→@Blocking\n    10→public class JaxRsApplication extends Application {\n    11→}\n    12→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"f46f3e45-40e2-4d79-b3d8-baac178c6f8e"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011dKLKAks6HdvVT2j1h9did","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateExtension;\n     4→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     5→import java.time.format.DateTimeFormatter;\n     6→\n     7→/**\n     8→ * This is a temporary hack around\n     9→ * <a href=\"https://github.com/redhat-developer-demos/quarkus-petclinic/issues/7\">this</a> issue.\n    10→ * <p>\n    11→ * The problem appears to be M1 specific and is being\n    12→ * <a href=\"https://quarkusio.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/187038-dev/topic/petclinic\">looked</a> into by the Quarkus devs.\n    13→ */\n    14→@TemplateExtension\n    15→public class Temporals {\n    16→\n    17→    private static final DateTimeFormatter FORMATTER = DateTimeFormatter.ofPattern(\"yyyy-MM-dd\");\n    18→\n    19→    public static String format(LocalDate localDate) {\n    20→        return localDate.format(FORMATTER);\n    21→    }\n    22→}\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"55f84e9d-db52-4dfb-b143-89261612e647"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JSfkwort3zGZcjTffAUaz4","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.model;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheEntity;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.MappedSuperclass;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n     8→\n     9→\n    10→@MappedSuperclass\n    11→public class Person extends PanacheEntity {\n    12→    \n    13→    @Column(name = \"first_name\")\n    14→    @NotEmpty\n    15→    @FormParam(\"firstName\")\n    16→    public String firstName;\n    17→\n    18→    @Column(name = \"last_name\")\n    19→    @NotEmpty\n    20→    @FormParam(\"lastName\")\n    21→    public String lastName;\n    22→\n    23→    @Override\n    24→    public String toString() {\n    25→        return \"Person [firstName=\" + firstName + \", lastName=\" + lastName + \"]\";\n    26→    }\n    27→\n    28→}\n    29→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"4cfad85a-6e6d-4903-bb75-e71b1318ba92"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NkrfsQQk3phHWG2tqP4coK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Collection;\n     4→import java.util.HashSet;\n     5→import java.util.Set;\n     6→\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.CascadeType;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.FetchType;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.OneToMany;\n    12→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    13→import jakarta.validation.constraints.Digits;\n    14→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    16→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.model.Person;\n    17→\n    18→@Entity\n    19→@Table(name = \"owners\")\n    20→public class Owner extends Person {\n    21→\n    22→    @Column(name = \"address\")\n    23→    @NotEmpty\n    24→    @FormParam(\"address\")\n    25→    public String address;\n    26→\n    27→    @Column(name = \"city\")\n    28→    @NotEmpty\n    29→    @FormParam(\"city\")\n    30→    public String city;\n    31→\n    32→    @Column(name = \"telephone\")\n    33→    @NotEmpty\n    34→    @Digits(fraction = 0, integer = 10)\n    35→    @FormParam(\"telephone\")\n    36→    public String telephone;\n    37→\n    38→    @OneToMany(cascade = CascadeType.ALL, mappedBy = \"owner\", fetch = FetchType.EAGER) // it is eager but probably it could be changed to lazy and make some lazy load before rendering template but we might end up in similar performance\n    39→    public Set<Pet> pets;\n    40→\n    41→    public static Collection<Owner> findByLastName(String name) {\n    42→        return Owner.list(\"lastName\", name);\n    43→    }\n    44→\n    45→    public Owner attach() {\n    46→        return getEntityManager().merge(this);\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    @Override\n    50→    public String toString() {\n    51→        return \"Owner [address=\" + address + \", city=\" + city + \", pets=\" + pets + \", telephone=\" + telephone + \"]\";\n    52→    }\n    53→\n    54→    public void addPet(Pet pet) {\n    55→        getPetsInternal().add(pet);\n    56→        pet.owner = this;\n    57→    }\n    58→\n    59→    protected Set<Pet> getPetsInternal() {\n    60→\t\tif (this.pets == null) {\n    61→\t\t\tthis.pets = new HashSet<>();\n    62→\t\t}\n    63→\t\treturn this.pets;\n    64→\t}\n    65→\n    66→}\n    67→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"555a8521-0773-4967-b16d-733da930273f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014YQn3jbQ62j25JsVWibZ1e","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n     5→\n     6→public class OwnerForm {\n     7→    \n     8→    @FormParam(\"firstName\")\n     9→    public String firstName;\n    10→\n    11→    @FormParam(\"lastName\")\n    12→    public String lastName;\n    13→\n    14→    @Override\n    15→    public String toString() {\n    16→        return \"OwnerForm [firstName=\" + firstName + \", lastName=\" + lastName + \"]\";\n    17→    }\n    18→\n    19→}\n    20→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"0a45dad5-8394-45bc-9684-03ce5413fd5a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0126MUPB9CM5dDY1GxNiVkbH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.BeanParam;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.QueryParam;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    15→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system.TemplatesLocale;\n    16→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    17→\n    18→import java.util.Arrays;\n    19→import java.util.Collection;\n    20→import java.util.Collections;\n    21→import java.util.HashMap;\n    22→import java.util.List;\n    23→import java.util.Map;\n    24→import java.util.Set;\n    25→\n    26→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n    27→\n    28→@Path(\"/owners\")\n    29→public class OwnersResource {\n    30→\n    31→    @Inject\n    32→    TemplatesLocale templates;\n    33→\n    34→    @Inject\n    35→    Validator validator;\n    36→\n    37→    @GET\n    38→    @Path(\"/find\")\n    39→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    40→    /**\n    41→     * Renders the findOwners.html\n    42→     * \n    43→     * @return\n    44→     */\n    45→    public TemplateInstance findTemplate() {\n    46→        return templates.findOwners(Collections.EMPTY_LIST);\n    47→    }\n    48→\n    49→    @GET\n    50→    @Path(\"new\")\n    51→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    52→    /**\n    53→     * Renders the createOrUpdateOwnerForm.html\n    54→     * \n    55→     * @return\n    56→     */\n    57→    public TemplateInstance createTemplate() {\n    58→        return templates.createOrUpdateOwnerForm(null, new HashMap<>());\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    @GET\n    62→    @Path(\"{ownerId}/edit\")\n    63→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    64→    /**\n    65→     * Renders the createOrUpdateOwnerForm.html\n    66→     * \n    67→     * @return\n    68→     */\n    69→    public TemplateInstance editTemplate(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId) {\n    70→        return templates.createOrUpdateOwnerForm(Owner.findById(ownerId), new  HashMap<>());\n    71→    }\n    72→\n    73→    @GET\n    74→    @Path(\"{ownerId}\")\n    75→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    76→    /**\n    77→     * Renders the createOrUpdateOwnerForm.html\n    78→     * \n    79→     * @return\n    80→     */\n    81→    public TemplateInstance showOwner(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId) {\n    82→        return templates.ownerDetails(Owner.findById(ownerId));\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    @POST\n    86→    @Path(\"new\")\n    87→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    88→    @Transactional\n    89→    /**\n    90→     * Renders the createOrUpdateOwnerForm.html\n    91→     * \n    92→     * @return\n    93→     */\n    94→    public TemplateInstance processCreationForm(@BeanParam Owner owner) {\n    95→        final Set<ConstraintViolation<Owner>> violations = validator.validate(owner);\n    96→        final Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n    97→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n    98→            \n    99→            for (ConstraintViolation<Owner> violation : violations) {\n   100→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n   101→            }\n   102→\n   103→            return templates.createOrUpdateOwnerForm(null, errors);\n   104→\n   105→        } else {\n   106→            owner.persist();\n   107→            return templates.ownerDetails(owner);\n   108→        }\n   109→    }\n   110→    \n   111→    @POST\n   112→    @Path(\"{ownerId}/edit\")\n   113→    @Transactional\n   114→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   115→    /**\n   116→     * Renders the createOrUpdateOwnerForm.html\n   117→     * \n   118→     * @return\n   119→     */\n   120→    public TemplateInstance processUpdateOwnerForm(@BeanParam Owner owner, @PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId) {\n   121→        final Set<ConstraintViolation<Owner>> violations = validator.validate(owner);\n   122→        final Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n   123→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n   124→            \n   125→            for (ConstraintViolation<Owner> violation : violations) {\n   126→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n   127→            }\n   128→\n   129→            return templates.createOrUpdateOwnerForm(owner, errors);\n   130→\n   131→        } else {\n   132→            // We need to reattach the Owner object. Since method is transactional, the update occurs automatically.\n   133→            return templates.ownerDetails(owner.attach());\n   134→        }\n   135→    }\n   136→\n   137→    @GET\n   138→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   139→    /**\n   140→     * Process the findOwners form\n   141→     */\n   142→    public TemplateInstance processFindForm(@QueryParam(\"lastName\") String lastName) {\n   143→\n   144→        Collection<Owner> owners = null;\n   145→\n   146→        // allow parameterless GET request for /owners to return all records\n   147→        if (lastName == null || \"\".equals(lastName.trim())) {\n   148→            owners = Owner.listAll(); // empty string signifies broadest possible search\n   149→        } else {\n   150→            owners = Owner.findByLastName(lastName);\n   151→        }\n   152→\n   153→        // find owners by last name\n   154→        if (owners.isEmpty()) {\n   155→            // no owners found\n   156→            return templates.findOwners(Arrays.asList(\"lastName not found\"));\n   157→        }\n   158→        if (owners.size() == 1) {\n   159→            // 1 owner found\n   160→            Owner owner = owners.iterator().next();\n   161→            return templates.ownerDetails(setVisits(owner));\n   162→        }\n   163→        \n   164→        return templates.ownersList(owners);\n   165→\n   166→    }\n   167→\n   168→    protected Owner setVisits(Owner owner) {\n   169→        for (Pet pet : owner.pets) {\n   170→            pet.setVisitsInternal(Visit.findByPetId(pet.id));\n   171→        }\n   172→        return owner;\n   173→    }\n   174→\n   175→    @Path(\"/api/list\")\n   176→    @GET\n   177→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   178→    public List<Owner> listOwners() {\n   179→        return Owner.listAll();\n   180→    }\n   181→\n   182→}\n   183→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"52021e8e-4fa5-4172-9512-b4c8f97ed824"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_014gTrRai9LifePDC2nvmgXp","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     5→import java.util.Collection;\n     6→import java.util.Collections;\n     7→import java.util.HashSet;\n     8→import java.util.LinkedHashSet;\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→import java.util.Set;\n    11→\n    12→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n    13→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    14→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    15→import jakarta.persistence.ManyToOne;\n    16→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    17→import jakarta.persistence.Transient;\n    18→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    19→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    20→\n    21→import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.JsonBackReference;\n    22→import io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheEntity;\n    23→\n    24→@Entity\n    25→@Table(name = \"pets\")\n    26→public class Pet extends PanacheEntity {\n    27→    \n    28→\t@Column(name = \"name\")\n    29→\t@NotEmpty\n    30→    public String name;\n    31→\n    32→\t@Column(name = \"birth_date\")\n    33→\tpublic LocalDate birthDate;\n    34→\n    35→\t@ManyToOne\n    36→\t@JoinColumn(name = \"type_id\")\n    37→\tpublic PetType type;\n    38→\n    39→\t@ManyToOne\n    40→\t@JoinColumn(name = \"owner_id\")\n    41→\t@JsonBackReference\n    42→\tpublic Owner owner;\n    43→\n    44→\t@Transient\n    45→\tpublic Set<Visit> visits = new LinkedHashSet<>();\n    46→\n    47→\tpublic Pet attach() {\n    48→        return getEntityManager().merge(this);\n    49→    }\n    50→\n    51→    protected Set<Visit> getVisitsInternal() {\n    52→\t\tif (this.visits == null) {\n    53→\t\t\tthis.visits = new HashSet<>();\n    54→\t\t}\n    55→\t\treturn this.visits;\n    56→\t}\n    57→\n    58→\tprotected void setVisitsInternal(Collection<Visit> visits) {\n    59→\t\tthis.visits = new LinkedHashSet<>(visits);\n    60→\t}\n    61→\n    62→\tpublic List<Visit> getSortedVisits() {\n    63→\t\tList<Visit> sortedVisits = new ArrayList<>(getVisitsInternal());\n    64→\t\tCollections.sort(sortedVisits, new VisitComparator());\n    65→\t\treturn Collections.unmodifiableList(sortedVisits);\n    66→\t}\n    67→\n    68→\tpublic void addVisit(Visit visit) {\n    69→\t\tgetVisitsInternal().add(visit);\n    70→\t\tvisit.petId = this.id;\n    71→    }\n    72→    \n    73→    public boolean isNew() {\n    74→\t\treturn this.id == null;\n    75→\t}\n    76→\n    77→\t@Override\n    78→\tpublic String toString() {\n    79→\t\treturn \"Pet [birthDate=\" + birthDate + \", name=\" + name + \", type=\" + type + \"]\";\n    80→\t}\n    81→\n    82→}\n    83→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"007ecaa4-b455-457c-98d3-2aa25ba6704b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_012KG35WUvpWhfyw8iKpzLmW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     5→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\n     7→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    15→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system.TemplatesLocale;\n    16→\n    17→import java.time.LocalDate;\n    18→import java.util.HashMap;\n    19→import java.util.Map;\n    20→import java.util.Set;\n    21→\n    22→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n    23→\n    24→@Path(\"/owners\")\n    25→public class PetResource {\n    26→    \n    27→    @Inject\n    28→    TemplatesLocale templates;\n    29→\n    30→    @Inject\n    31→    Validator validator;\n    32→\n    33→    @GET\n    34→    @Path(\"{ownerId}/pets/new\")\n    35→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    36→    public TemplateInstance createTemplate(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId) {\n    37→        return templates.createOrUpdatePetForm(Owner.findById(ownerId), null, PetType.listAll(), new HashMap<>());\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    @GET\n    41→    @Path(\"{ownerId}/pets/{petId}/edit\")\n    42→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    43→    public TemplateInstance editTemplate(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId, @PathParam(\"petId\") Long petId) {\n    44→        return templates.createOrUpdatePetForm(Owner.findById(ownerId), Pet.findById(petId), PetType.listAll(), new HashMap<>());\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    @POST\n    48→    @Path(\"{ownerId}/pets/new\")\n    49→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    50→    @Transactional\n    51→    public TemplateInstance processCreationForm(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId, @FormParam(\"name\") String name, @FormParam(\"birthDate\") LocalDate birthDate, @FormParam(\"type\") String type) {\n    52→        Owner owner = Owner.findById(ownerId);\n    53→        \n    54→        Pet pet = new Pet();\n    55→        pet.birthDate = birthDate;\n    56→        pet.name = name;\n    57→        pet.type = PetType.parse(type);\n    58→\n    59→\n    60→        final Set<ConstraintViolation<Pet>> violations = validator.validate(pet);\n    61→        final Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n    62→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n    63→            \n    64→            for (ConstraintViolation<Pet> violation : violations) {\n    65→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n    66→            }\n    67→\n    68→            return templates.createOrUpdatePetForm(Owner.findById(ownerId), null, PetType.listAll(), errors);\n    69→\n    70→        } else {\n    71→\n    72→            pet.persist();\n    73→            owner.addPet(pet);\n    74→            return templates.ownerDetails(owner);\n    75→        }\n    76→    }\n    77→\n    78→    @POST\n    79→    @Path(\"{ownerId}/pets/{petId}/edit\")\n    80→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    81→    @Transactional\n    82→    public TemplateInstance processUpdateForm(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId, @PathParam(\"petId\") Long petId, @FormParam(\"name\") String name, @FormParam(\"birthDate\") LocalDate birthDate, @FormParam(\"type\") String type) {\n    83→        Pet pet = new Pet();\n    84→        pet.id = petId;\n    85→        pet.birthDate = birthDate;\n    86→        pet.name = name;\n    87→        pet.type = PetType.parse(type);\n    88→\n    89→        final Set<ConstraintViolation<Pet>> violations = validator.validate(pet);\n    90→        final Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n    91→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n    92→            \n    93→            for (ConstraintViolation<Pet> violation : violations) {\n    94→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n    95→            }\n    96→\n    97→            Pet oldPet = Pet.findById(petId);\n    98→            return templates.createOrUpdatePetForm(oldPet.owner, oldPet, PetType.listAll(), errors);\n    99→\n   100→        } else {\n   101→            return templates.ownerDetails(pet.attach().owner);\n   102→        }\n   103→    }\n   104→\n   105→}\n   106→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"4ea40f9e-1715-440c-ab78-14cd65d15225"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_015mhiD6wg4anrtQren9bL2K","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Collection;\n     4→\n     5→import io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheEntity;\n     6→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateExtension;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n     8→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    10→\n    11→@Entity\n    12→@Table(name = \"types\")\n    13→public class PetType extends PanacheEntity {\n    14→\n    15→\t@Column(name = \"name\")\n    16→\tpublic String name;\n    17→\n    18→\tpublic static PetType parse(String text) {\n    19→\t\tCollection<PetType> findPetTypes = PetType.listAll();\n    20→\t\tfor (PetType type : findPetTypes) {\n    21→\t\t\tif (type.name.equals(text)) {\n    22→\t\t\t\treturn type;\n    23→\t\t\t}\n    24→\t\t}\n    25→\t\tthrow new IllegalArgumentException(\"type not found: \" + text);\n    26→\t}\n    27→\n    28→}\n    29→\n    30→@TemplateExtension\n    31→class Formatter {\n    32→\tstatic String stringify(PetType petType) {\n    33→\t\treturn petType.name;\n    34→\t}\n    35→\n    36→}\n    37→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"505361f3-04c4-41d5-b49c-74eb409198fd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01HHGom2BqbHXkQFCN9qsJm8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Comparator;\n     4→\n     5→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n     6→\n     7→public class VisitComparator implements Comparator<Visit> {\n     8→\n     9→    @Override\n    10→    public int compare(Visit o1, Visit o2) {\n    11→        return o1.date.compareTo(o2.date);\n    12→    }\n    13→    \n    14→}\n    15→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"73ff1a83-673b-49d9-b8c8-f007c7ae3803"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BC9hf5cxGKk7ozD7dFAbaa","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\n     6→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.BeanParam;\n     8→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     9→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    14→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system.TemplatesLocale;\n    15→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    16→\n    17→import java.util.HashMap;\n    18→import java.util.Map;\n    19→import java.util.Set;\n    20→\n    21→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n    22→\n    23→@Path(\"/owners\")\n    24→public class VisitResource {\n    25→    \n    26→    @Inject\n    27→    TemplatesLocale templates;\n    28→\n    29→    @Inject\n    30→    Validator validator;\n    31→\n    32→    @GET\n    33→    @Path(\"{ownerId}/pets/{petId}/visits/new\")\n    34→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    35→    public TemplateInstance createTemplate(@PathParam(\"petId\") Long petId) {\n    36→        return templates.createOrUpdateVisitForm(Pet.findById(petId), null, new HashMap<>());\n    37→    }\n    38→\n    39→    @POST\n    40→    @Path(\"{ownerId}/pets/{petId}/visits/new\")\n    41→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    42→    @Transactional\n    43→    public TemplateInstance processCreationForm(@PathParam(\"petId\") Long petId,  @BeanParam Visit visit) {\n    44→\n    45→        Pet pet = Pet.findById(petId);\n    46→        final Set<ConstraintViolation<Visit>> violations = validator.validate(visit);\n    47→        final Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n    48→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n    49→            \n    50→            for (ConstraintViolation<Visit> violation : violations) {\n    51→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n    52→            }\n    53→\n    54→            return templates.createOrUpdateVisitForm(pet, visit, errors);\n    55→\n    56→        } else {\n    57→            \n    58→            visit.persist();\n    59→\n    60→            pet.addVisit(visit);\n    61→            return templates.ownerDetails(pet.owner);\n    62→        }\n    63→    }\n    64→\n    65→}\n    66→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"9445e7a3-0ea2-4626-8ca0-8f61ed6ce1d5"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01F4MMXtSyCQD4rbopP6AoXv","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ext.ParamConverter;\n     4→\n     5→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     6→\n     7→public class LocalDateConverter implements ParamConverter<LocalDate> {\n     8→\n     9→    @Override\n    10→    public LocalDate fromString(String value) {\n    11→        if (\"\".equals(value.trim()))\n    12→            return null;\n    13→        return LocalDate.parse(value);\n    14→    }\n    15→\n    16→    @Override\n    17→    public String toString(LocalDate value) {\n    18→        if (value == null)\n    19→            return null;\n    20→        return value.toString();\n    21→    }\n    22→\n    23→}\n    24→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"7b87ef1a-e8f0-4a26-a1f0-7b90499a6696"}
