{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01CcBCAUS2Z4QjWuuwciQR4K","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Collection;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.Map;\n     6→\n     7→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner.Owner;\n     8→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner.Pet;\n     9→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner.PetType;\n    10→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.vet.Vet;\n    11→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    12→\n    13→import io.quarkus.qute.CheckedTemplate;\n    14→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n    15→\n    16→@CheckedTemplate\n    17→public class Templates {\n    18→    public static native TemplateInstance welcome();\n    19→\n    20→    public static native TemplateInstance error(String message);\n    21→\n    22→    public static native TemplateInstance vetList(List<Vet> vets);\n    23→\n    24→    public static native TemplateInstance findOwners(List<String> errors);\n    25→\n    26→    public static native TemplateInstance ownerDetails(Owner owner);\n    27→\n    28→    public static native TemplateInstance createOrUpdateOwnerForm(Owner owner, Map<String, String> errors);\n    29→\n    30→    public static native TemplateInstance ownersList(Collection<Owner> owners);\n    31→\n    32→    public static native TemplateInstance createOrUpdatePetForm(Owner owner, Pet pet, List<PetType> petTypes, Map<String, String> errors);\n    33→\n    34→    public static native TemplateInstance createOrUpdateVisitForm(Pet pet, Visit visit, Map<String, String> errors);\n    35→}\n    36→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"86a4f888-8a9b-4015-8806-7c60ee01f9c6"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01DwGnUErmjcoUfH4PtU8kcV","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Collection;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→import java.util.Locale;\n     6→import java.util.Map;\n     7→\n     8→import jakarta.enterprise.context.ApplicationScoped;\n     9→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner.Owner;\n    10→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner.Pet;\n    11→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner.PetType;\n    12→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.vet.Vet;\n    13→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    14→\n    15→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n    16→\n    17→@ApplicationScoped\n    18→public class TemplatesLocale {\n    19→    \n    20→    public TemplateInstance welcome() {\n    21→        return Templates.welcome().setAttribute(\"locale\", getConfiguredLocale());\n    22→    }\n    23→\n    24→    public TemplateInstance error(String message) {\n    25→        return Templates.error(message).setAttribute(\"locale\", getConfiguredLocale());\n    26→    }\n    27→\n    28→    public TemplateInstance vetList(List<Vet> vets) {\n    29→        return Templates.vetList(vets).setAttribute(\"locale\", getConfiguredLocale());\n    30→    }\n    31→\n    32→    public TemplateInstance findOwners(List<String> errors) {\n    33→        return Templates.findOwners(errors).setAttribute(\"locale\", getConfiguredLocale());\n    34→    }\n    35→\n    36→    public TemplateInstance ownerDetails(Owner owner) {\n    37→        return Templates.ownerDetails(owner).setAttribute(\"locale\", getConfiguredLocale());\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    public TemplateInstance createOrUpdateOwnerForm(Owner owner, Map<String, String> errors) {\n    41→        return Templates.createOrUpdateOwnerForm(owner, errors).setAttribute(\"locale\", getConfiguredLocale());\n    42→    }\n    43→\n    44→    public TemplateInstance ownersList(Collection<Owner> owners) {\n    45→        return Templates.ownersList(owners).setAttribute(\"locale\", getConfiguredLocale());\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    public TemplateInstance createOrUpdatePetForm(Owner owner, Pet pet, List<PetType> petTypes, Map<String, String> errors) {\n    49→        return Templates.createOrUpdatePetForm(owner, pet, petTypes, errors).setAttribute(\"locale\", getConfiguredLocale());\n    50→    }\n    51→\n    52→    public TemplateInstance createOrUpdateVisitForm(Pet pet, Visit visit, Map<String, String> errors) {\n    53→        return Templates.createOrUpdateVisitForm(pet, visit, errors).setAttribute(\"locale\", getConfiguredLocale());\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    protected Locale getConfiguredLocale() {\n    57→        return  Locale.getDefault();\n    58→    }\n    59→\n    60→}\n    61→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"88ff2873-5742-4d5b-83c6-54ffc7c39117"}
