{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016UueCPwYEFVetFVpsvDjcu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.vet;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheEntity;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n     7→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n     8→\n     9→@Entity\n    10→@Table(name = \"specialties\")\n    11→public class Specialty extends PanacheEntity {\n    12→\n    13→    @Column(name = \"name\")\n    14→    public String name;\n    15→\n    16→    @Override\n    17→    public String toString() {\n    18→        return \"Specialty [name=\" + name + \"]\";\n    19→    }\n    20→\n    21→}\n    22→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"7f8e18e4-e093-4555-bde9-5fe30e531abd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FbxjKnA1tVS2K1mi3DC4nD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.vet;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.Comparator;\n     4→\n     5→public class SpecialityComparator implements Comparator<Specialty> {\n     6→\n     7→    @Override\n     8→    public int compare(Specialty o1, Specialty o2) {\n     9→        return o1.name.compareTo(o2.name);\n    10→    }\n    11→    \n    12→}\n    13→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"41e5963b-fb22-4b74-8549-0d8b0dce710f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Twbn6nmRP7Kd9wzyajucZS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.vet;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     4→import java.util.Collections;\n     5→import java.util.HashSet;\n     6→import java.util.List;\n     7→import java.util.Set;\n     8→\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.FetchType;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.JoinColumn;\n    12→import jakarta.persistence.JoinTable;\n    13→import jakarta.persistence.ManyToMany;\n    14→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    15→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.model.Person;\n    16→\n    17→@Entity\n    18→@Table(name = \"vets\")\n    19→public class Vet extends Person {\n    20→    \n    21→    @ManyToMany(fetch = FetchType.EAGER)\n    22→\t@JoinTable(name = \"vet_specialties\", joinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = \"vet_id\"),\n    23→\t\t\tinverseJoinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = \"specialty_id\"))\n    24→\tpublic Set<Specialty> specialties;\n    25→\n    26→\tprotected Set<Specialty> getSpecialtiesInternal() {\n    27→\t\tif (this.specialties == null) {\n    28→\t\t\tthis.specialties = new HashSet<>();\n    29→\t\t}\n    30→\t\treturn this.specialties;\n    31→\t}\n    32→\n    33→\tpublic List<Specialty> getSpecialties() {\n    34→\t\tList<Specialty> sortedSpecs = new ArrayList<>(getSpecialtiesInternal());\n    35→\t\tCollections.sort(sortedSpecs, new SpecialityComparator());\n    36→\t\treturn Collections.unmodifiableList(sortedSpecs);\n    37→\t}\n    38→\n    39→\tpublic int getNrOfSpecialties() {\n    40→\t\treturn getSpecialtiesInternal().size();\n    41→\t}\n    42→\n    43→\tpublic void addSpecialty(Specialty specialty) {\n    44→\t\tgetSpecialtiesInternal().add(specialty);\n    45→\t}\n    46→\n    47→\t@Override\n    48→\tpublic String toString() {\n    49→\t\treturn super.toString() + \" Vet [specialties=\" + specialties + \"]\";\n    50→\t}\n    51→\n    52→\t\n    53→\n    54→}\n    55→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"d0c0e3e0-acb9-4197-a8fd-93fa3875680b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01KfMEm5zTuDVmYSpo2KWZ6h","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.vet;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n     5→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n     6→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n     7→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n     8→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system.Templates;\n     9→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.system.TemplatesLocale;\n    10→\n    11→import io.quarkus.qute.TemplateInstance;\n    12→\n    13→import java.util.List;\n    14→\n    15→@Path(\"/\")\n    16→public class VetResource {\n    17→    \n    18→    @Inject\n    19→    TemplatesLocale templates;\n    20→\n    21→    @GET\n    22→    @Path(\"/vets.html\")\n    23→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    24→    public TemplateInstance showResourcesVetPage() {\n    25→        List<Vet> vets = Vet.listAll();\n    26→        System.out.println(vets);\n    27→        return templates.vetList(vets);\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    @GET\n    31→    @Path(\"/vets\")\n    32→    public Vets showResourcesVetList() {\n    33→        Vets vets = new Vets();\n    34→\t\tvets.getVetList().addAll(Vet.listAll());\n    35→\t\treturn vets;\n    36→    }\n    37→\n    38→}\n    39→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"233a48ef-9232-4dcb-9933-93487ac0177a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01QFusTA5PXRA56ciHMeqpfD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.vet;\n     2→\n     3→import java.util.ArrayList;\n     4→import java.util.List;\n     5→\n     6→public class Vets {\n     7→    \n     8→    private List<Vet> vets;\n     9→\n    10→\tpublic List<Vet> getVetList() {\n    11→\t\tif (vets == null) {\n    12→\t\t\tvets = new ArrayList<>();\n    13→\t\t}\n    14→\t\treturn vets;\n    15→\t}\n    16→\n    17→}\n    18→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"24dcfb20-6c7f-4581-a317-9a0e1e2a1c07"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01GpkCnrfQTpsy9hnKwoEkep","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.visit;\n     2→\n     3→import java.time.LocalDate;\n     4→import java.util.Collection;\n     5→\n     6→\n     7→\n     8→import io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheEntity;\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.Column;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.Entity;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.Table;\n    12→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotEmpty;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    14→\n    15→@Entity\n    16→@Table(name = \"visits\")\n    17→public class Visit extends PanacheEntity {\n    18→    \n    19→\t@Column(name = \"visit_date\")\n    20→\t@FormParam(\"date\")\n    21→\tpublic LocalDate date;\n    22→\n    23→\t@NotEmpty\n    24→\t@Column(name = \"description\")\n    25→\t@FormParam(\"description\")\n    26→\tpublic String description;\n    27→\n    28→\t@Column(name = \"pet_id\")\n    29→\tpublic Long petId;\n    30→\n    31→\tpublic static Collection<Visit> findByPetId(Long petId) {\n    32→        return Visit.list(\"petId\", petId);\n    33→    }\n    34→}\n    35→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"3ae74288-39f8-43ba-9a79-df821bba12d8"}
