{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BmghS6qQAXAGqqvfApoWWb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<!doctype html>\n     2→<html>\n     3→\n     4→<head>\n     5→\n     6→  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\" />\n     7→  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n     8→  <meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\n     9→  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n    10→\n    11→  <title>PetClinic :: a Quarkus Framework demonstration</title>\n    12→\n    13→  <!--[if lt IE 9]>\n    14→    <script src=\"https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.2/html5shiv.min.js\"></script>\n    15→    <script src=\"https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js\"></script>\n    16→    <![endif]-->\n    17→  <link rel=\"shortcut icon\" type=\"image/x-icon\" href=\"/images/favicon.ico\">\n    18→  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/webjars/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css\">\n    19→  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/css/petclinic.css\" />\n    20→\n    21→</head>\n    22→\n    23→<body>\n    24→\n    25→  <nav class=\"navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark\" role=\"navigation\">\n    26→    <div class=\"container\">\n    27→      <div class=\"navbar-header\">\n    28→        <a class=\"navbar-brand\" href=\"/\"><span></span></a>\n    29→        <button class=\"navbar-toggler\" type=\"button\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#main-navbar\">\n    30→          <span class=\"navbar-toggler-icon\"></span>\n    31→        </button>\n    32→      </div>\n    33→      <div class=\"collapse navbar-collapse\" id=\"main-navbar\" style>\n    34→\n    35→        <ul class=\"nav navbar-nav me-auto\">\n    36→\n    37→          <li class=\"active\">\n    38→            <a href=\"/\" title=\"home page\">\n    39→              <span class=\"fa fa-home\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    40→              <span>{msg:home}</span>\n    41→            </a>\n    42→          </li>\n    43→\n    44→          <li>\n    45→            <a href=\"/owners/find\" title=\"find owners\">\n    46→              <span class=\"fa fa-search\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    47→              <span>{msg:find_owners}</span>\n    48→            </a>\n    49→          </li>\n    50→\n    51→          <li>\n    52→            <a href=\"/vets.html\" title=\"veterinarians\">\n    53→              <span class=\"fa fa-th-list\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    54→              <span>{msg:veterinarians}</span>\n    55→            </a>\n    56→          </li>\n    57→\n    58→          <li>\n    59→            <a href=\"/oups\" title=\"trigger a RuntimeException to see how it is handled\">\n    60→              <span class=\"fa exclamation-triangle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    61→              <span>{msg:error}</span>\n    62→            </a>\n    63→          </li>\n    64→\n    65→        </ul>\n    66→      </div>\n    67→    </div>\n    68→  </nav>\n    69→  <div class=\"container-fluid\">\n    70→    <div class=\"container xd-container\">\n    71→\n    72→      {#insert body}No body!{/} \n    73→\n    74→    </div>\n    75→  </div>\n    76→\n    77→  <script src=\"/webjars/bootstrap/5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js\"></script>\n    78→\n    79→</body>\n    80→\n    81→</html>\n    82→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"f138d14f-38e2-4439-a558-bbdb12a23e06"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01S7Tj42ULaojWK8wwjCSzkE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base} \n     2→  {#body}\n     3→  <h2>{msg:welcome}</h2>\n     4→  <div class=\"row\">\n     5→      <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n     6→        <img class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"../images/pets.png\"/>\n     7→      </div>\n     8→  </div>\n     9→  {/body}\n    10→{/include}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"c409eb3d-cda8-4774-8f41-180a52c3764a"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011FkYtFKy57JgR9qSDF82LE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base} \n     2→  {#body}\n     3→  <h2>{msg:find_owners}</h2>\n     4→\n     5→  <form action=\"/owners\" method=\"get\"\n     6→    class=\"form-horizontal\" id=\"search-owner-form\">\n     7→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n     8→      <div class=\"control-group\" id=\"lastNameGroup\">\n     9→        <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:last_name} </label>\n    10→        <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    11→          <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\" id=\"lastName\" name=\"lastName\" size=\"30\"\n    12→            maxlength=\"80\" />\n    13→            {#if errors.size > 0} \n    14→            <span class=\"help-inline\">\n    15→                <div>\n    16→                    {#for err in errors}\n    17→                        <p>{err}</p>\n    18→                    {/for}\n    19→                </div>\n    20→            </div>\n    21→            </span>\n    22→            {/if}\n    23→        </div>\n    24→      </div>\n    25→    </div>\n    26→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    27→      <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    28→        <button type=\"submit\" class=\"btn btn-primary\">{msg:find_owner}</button>\n    29→      </div>\n    30→    </div>\n    31→\n    32→    <a class=\"btn btn-primary\" href=\"/owners/new\">{msg:add_owner}</a>\n    33→\n    34→  </form>\n    35→\n    36→  {/body}\n    37→{/include}\n    38→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"cb22f2a3-ff4c-45d5-b6df-64