{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01YFfzDxZGM58AAvLx4sU2ak","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→<h2>\n     4→    {#if !visit}{msg:new_} {/if}\n     5→    {msg:visit}\n     6→</h2>\n     7→\n     8→<b>Pet</b>\n     9→<table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    10→    <thead>\n    11→        <tr>\n    12→            <th>{msg:name}</th>\n    13→            <th>{msg:birthdate}</th>\n    14→            <th>{msg:type}</th>\n    15→            <th>{msg:owner}</th>\n    16→        </tr>\n    17→    </thead>\n    18→    <tr>\n    19→        <td>{pet.name}</td>\n    20→        <td>{pet.birthDate.format()}</td>\n    21→        <td>{pet.type.name}</td>\n    22→        <td>{pet.owner.firstName} {pet.owner.lastName}</td>\n    23→    </tr>\n    24→</table>\n    25→\n    26→<form class=\"form-horizontal\" method=\"post\">\n    27→    <div class=\"form-group has-feedback\">\n    28→\n    29→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('date') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    30→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:date}</label>\n    31→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    32→                <div>\n    33→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"YYYY-MM-DD\"\n    34→                        id=\"date\" name=\"date\" value=\"{visit.date ?: ''}\"/>\n    35→                </div>\n    36→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('date') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    37→                {#if errors.containsKey('date') != null}\n    38→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('date')}</span>\n    39→                {/if}\n    40→            </div>\n    41→        </div>\n    42→\n    43→\n    44→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('description') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    45→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:description}</label>\n    46→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    47→                <div>\n    48→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"description\" name=\"description\" value=\"{visit.description ?: ''}\" />\n    49→                </div>\n    50→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('description') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    51→                {#if errors.containsKey('description') != null}\n    52→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('description')}</span>\n    53→                {/if}\n    54→            </div>\n    55→        </div>\n    56→\n    57→    </div>\n    58→\n    59→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    60→        <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    61→            <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"petId\" value=\"1\" />\n    62→            <button class=\"btn btn-primary\" type=\"submit\">{msg:add_visit}</button>\n    63→        </div>\n    64→    </div>\n    65→</form>\n    66→\n    67→<br />\n    68→<b>{msg:previous_visits}</b>\n    69→<table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    70→    <tr>\n    71→        <th>{msg:date}</th>\n    72→        <th>{msg:description}</th>\n    73→    </tr>\n    74→    <tr>\n    75→        {#if visit}\n    76→        {#for v in pet.sortedVisits}\n    77→        <td>{v.date.format()}</td>\n    78→        <td>{v.description}</td>\n    79→        {/for}\n    80→        {/if}\n    81→    </tr>\n    82→</table>\n    83→{/body}\n    84→{/include}\n    85→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}