{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01MXSp3cSfZqfAV9wKi1GMtX","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I see the issue. The data is being loaded twice - once by Hibernate's `ddl-auto=create-drop` (which seems to also be running the data.sql) and then again by Spring's script initialization. The problem is that `spring.jpa.defer-datasource-initialization=true` causes data.sql to run after Hibernate creates the schema, but Hibernate may also be importing data through its own mechanism. The fix is to ensure data.sql only runs after schema creation and doesn't conflict. The issue is a duplicate key constraint.\n\nThe simplest fix: change the `INSERT INTO` to `INSERT INTO ... ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` or just stop using `spring.jpa.defer-datasource-initialization=true` and use Hibernate's `import.sql` instead:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7559,"cache_read_input_tokens":135928,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7559,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":285},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d5033181-b1d4-4ac6-8656-753e13eb13fa","uuid":"26f55e15-108f-4daf-8c2b-ef8157042d75"}
